review_blob: Brown/cherry color, dark & beautiful. Head builds up, then just hangs there like a runny nose. Hoppie aroma. Sweet grapefruit also tickles the nostrils. Bitter is the 1st taste I get. Thats good. Me like the bitter. Smooth yet light texture. Smells like it tastes. Yum! Taste lingers on the after exhales. Nice. Not bad. Not the best.

Brown/cola brown. Dark tan, thick head. Looks like a great beer. Hops galore. Brown sugar extras. Lemon & citrus, orange aromas. The off-beat sugar aromas smells unbalanced. Wow, what a pallet extravaganza. Smooth, tart, citrus & sugar. Creamy & nice. Excellent aftertaste.
beer_name: Bear Republic Hop Rod Rye Ale

review_blob: Thats what it is. Black. Beautiful head. Dark Head. Thick and rich, just stays, wow. Molasses, dark rich aroma. Sweet, like a port. Molasses , citrus flavor is what it does to the nose. Slightly a watery flavor, not as nice as the aroma & look. Needs to sit. I smell hops but dont taste them. Disappointing
beer_name: Bear Republic Big Bear Black Stout

review_blob: Dark, over-brewed coffee color, dark cream head. The head holds out, steady like a snot rocket. Lacing looks like African jungle love. Brown sugar,  malty aroma. Very well balanced. Stiff on the palate, again I taste metal. strong flavor matches the aroma. Tastes beautiful. Coffee aftertaste, coming through my nose. Great beer.
Orange butter in color...cream head floating in little islands on top. Hop aroma, done. Taste- bitter, un-even, and ewe. Not diggin it.
beer_name: Boulder Beer The GABF 25th Year Beer

review_blob: Great head. Hoppy aroma. Great balance nice texture, cream. Lovely and delicious gold color with cloudiness. nice beer

Light color-white head. Yeast aroma, smells like alcohol. Fruity like berries. Strong flavor, tastes like liqueur, nice aftertaste. Stays on the palate. Another surprising beer. Light looking, but strong on the palate. Doesnt linger long. Nice lacing. Head goes on and on.

Very cloudy-unfiltered. Golden color, light yellowy cream head. delicate lacing. Lemony and apple aromas. Excites the nostrils. Strong hops, not bitter in the aftertaste. Lemon invigorates the palate. Good flavor. Nice IPA. Beer is very pretty.

Dark brown, dark tan head. Smells of many fruits, molasses, and brown sugar. Sweet and bitter. - Hoppy. Can taste the sugars. Coffee or espresso on the exhale. Very nice stout. Kinda what you expect. Strong and robust. Slight alcohol aroma, but surprised to see how high the content is. Love it!

Yeasty aroma. Color is gold. White head. Has a metallic aftertaste. Doesnt last long on palate, but stays in your nose. Not one of the best German beers, but for the price- not too bad. I taste steel.
Smells like...well it smells. Very unbalanced odor. Even worst taste. Leaves a gnats piss taste in your mouth. Gross gross gross. Color is dark golden Head is cream color. Good college beer.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Dark yellow amber color. Dark cream colored head, light and frothy. Lacing is good in my glass. Sweet aroma, fruity, cherries & apricots fill my nostrils. Good after taste Lingers on the palate. Makes my mouth happy. Light and yummy Nice beer.

Beautiful color. Red-cranberry color. Pink head. Cherries, cherries, cherries. Sweet aroma trickles the nose. Sweet taste- like a candy, cherry jolly rancher. Light and refreshing. Sour. Beautiful flavor. Yummo!  Champagne feelings on my tongue. Best beer all night.

Dark caramel color with beige head (like the head) looks pretty in glass. Smells of lemons and other citrus with yeast. Sweet and bitter, it balances on the tongue. Tasting slight sour overtones. Really like the flavor of this ale strong in my mouth. Hits me hard as is flows down my throat.

Burnt sienna color, head is sparse through the glass, when agitated, the head comes to life, then falls away to its island of dreams. Orange flavors fill my nose, its the smells of summer in a glass light and balanced. Champagne bubbles lift from the center of my glass. Creamy happiness fills my mouth. Citrus flavors flow through my palate. The aroma touching my soul. Flavorful light and refreshing- great sumer beer.
Good beer; could drink at a party; also could drink to appreciate. I wish the flavor would last longer on the tounge. Not Bad. I enjoyed it, agaist others I have tasted.
